OL,3,CRNLI warning over rip currents after
OL,4,Cfour swimmers rescued in Cornwall
OL,6,FTregonhawke RNLI lifeguards responded
OL,7,Fto 13 incidents between 3`8 April,
OL,8,Fincluding one rescue, eight assists,
OL,9,Fand 114 near misses, many involving
OL,10,Fswimmers caught in developing rip
OL,11,Fcurrents.
OL,13,FRNLI Lead Lifeguard Supervisor Charlie
OL,14,FGillett, warns of the dangers of rip
OL,15,Fcurrents: "Rip currents can be
OL,16,Fdifficult to spot, but are sometimes
OL,17,Fidentified by a channel of churning,
OL,18,Fchoppy water on the sea's surface.
OL,1,W~s1j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/4
